The Ring goes from cold to KILLING cold; Orion can't move. Valerius is simply THERE
(sending/projection), unhurried:
  "You served me well. But understand what you are. You are a tool. An extension of my hand. And
  a hand that will not close when I will it..." — and he takes Orion's OFF-HAND, below the elbow.
  Permanent. (MECH: any minor action needing the off-hand becomes a MAJOR action until Orion gets
  a prosthesis.) "...is trimmed. Serve better."

GM: if you'd rather the road stay a respite, HOLD this — it lands just as hard at Ivarstead or
after. Flagging, not forcing. [flagged earlier]

=====================================================================
SCENE 7 — THE FAINT WRONGNESS (approach; transition out)
=====================================================================
The dragons are gone — banked away, dwindling, the sky empty again. Relief. And then, as the road
finally bends toward the mountain's foot, the first hairline crack in the world.

GM: Begin SONG OF THE SISTERS (Hans Zimmer) — Gaelen's theme — as the cart crests the saddle
and the dragons depart. Let it run under the descent and into the town segment.

READ ALOUD: "The two shadows shrink into the east and are gone, and the breath you didn't know
you were holding goes out of all of you at once. Nobody speaks. The relief is too large for
